) and

Discontinuance by a plaintiff does not necessarily affect proceedings on a defendant's cross-claim: Toyota Motor Corp Australia Ltd v Ken Morgan Motors Pty Ltd [1994] 2 VR 106 at 210 ; 
r 12.1(5)
 of the UCPR (proceedings on a cross-claim are taken to be different proceedings to the proceedings on the originating process and to proceedings on any other cross-claim); unless the cross-claim is merely consequential on the plaintiff's claim. However, a cross-claim cannot be raised after the discontinuance: The Salybia [1910] P 25 .
